Week 1 Objectives: Connect and get acquainted with members of First Cloud Journey. Understand basic AWS services, how to use the console &amp; CLI. Tasks to be carried out this week: Day Task Start Date Completion Date Reference Material 2 - Get acquainted with FCJ members and find a study group - Read and note internship rules and regulations - Learn about Cloud Computing &amp; AWS Global Infrastructure: + Cloud Computing: on-demand delivery of IT resources, pay-as-you-go + Benefits: Cost Optimization, Automation &amp; AI, Flexibility, Scale globally + AWS Data Center, Availability Zone (AZ), Region, Edge Locations - Create an AWS Free Tier account: + Register for an AWS account + Add a Visa card to receive 100 AWS credits 20/04/2026 20/04/2026 https://cloudjourney.awsstudygroup.com/ https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qVCF7UjYC5s&t=854s https://000001.awsstudygroup.com/ Week 1 Achievements: Understood Cloud Computing and AWS Global Infrastructure:
Cloud Computing: on-demand delivery of IT resources with pay-as-you-go pricing. Benefits: Cost Optimization, Automation &amp; AI, Flexibility, Scale globally. AWS Data Center: each data center contains tens of thousands of servers using dedicated AWS devices. Availability Zone (AZ): fault isolation — failure in one AZ does not affect another. AWS recommends deploying on a minimum of 2 AZs. Vietnamese customers mostly use Singapore AZ — a full outage is virtually unheard of. In practice: cost constraints may justify 1 AZ, but a backup plan to another AZ is mandatory. Region: minimum 3 AZs, 25+ Regions globally — SEA has 3: Singapore, Malaysia, Thailand. Edge Locations: CloudFront (CDN), WAF, Route 53. Successfully created and configured an AWS Free Tier account, added a Visa card, and received 100 AWS credits.
